The words module
================

This module handles some english words

	>>> from words import matchCase
	>>> print matchCase('ALAN','alanies')
	ALANIES
	>>> print matchCase('Alan','alanies')
	Alanies
	>>> print matchCase('alaN','alanies')
	alaNies
	>>> print matchCase('alan','alanies')
	alanies

	>>> from words import pluralize
	>>> print pluralize('fred')
	freds
	>>> print pluralize('freddy')
	freddies
	>>> print pluralize('punch')
	punches
	>>> print pluralize('fish')
	fish
	>>> print pluralize('index')
	indices
	>>> print pluralize('Index')
	Indices
	>>> print pluralize('lunch')
	lunches

	>>> print pluralize('bass')
	basses
	>>> print pluralize('fax')
	faxes
	>>> print pluralize('waltz')
	waltzes
	>>> print pluralize('coach')
	coaches
	>>> print pluralize('rash')
	rashes
	>>> print pluralize('cheetah')
	cheetahs
	>>> print pluralize('vacancy')
	vacancies
	>>> print pluralize('day')
	days

	>>> print pluralize('man')
	men
	>>> print pluralize('woman')
	women
	>>> print pluralize('human')
	humans
	>>> print pluralize('mouse')
	mice
	>>> print pluralize('louse')
	lice
	>>> print pluralize('house')
	houses
	>>> print pluralize('knife')
	knives
	>>> print pluralize('wife')
	wives
	>>> print pluralize('sheep')
	sheep
	>>> print pluralize('deer')
	deer
	>>> print pluralize('haiku')
	haiku
	>>> print pluralize('hero')
	heroes
	>>> print pluralize('piano')
	pianos

	>>> pluralize('lowlife') == 'lowlifes'
	False


	>>> from words import number_name
	>>> print number_name('one')
	one
	>>> print number_name('1')
	one
	>>> print number_name(1)
	one
	>>> print number_name(11)
	11

We can also get singular forms,
	but the method is called depluralize to emphasize that it just does the opposite of pluralize
	>>> from words import depluralize

Less milk from only one of these
	>>> print depluralize('cows')
	cow

But plenty of sailing at the only one of these
	>>> print depluralize('Cowes')
	Cowes

	>>> print depluralize('cats')
	cat

	>>> print depluralize('fish')
	fish
